               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1550" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1550" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1550" type="surname" value="SANDWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1550" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD SANDWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a publican, and live in High-street, Lambeth. On the 2nd of March the prisoner came for some beer—he tendered a half-crown—I put it into a bowl—there were a few sixpences there, but no other half-crown—I gave him change and he went away—a few minutes after I went to the till—there was no one there but me—I took out the half-crown, and found it was bad—I marked it and put it into my pocket—on the 4th he came again for a pint of porter—he tendered another half-crown—I saw it was bad—he went into the tap-room—I did not say any thing, but sent for an officer and gave him the two half-crowns.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
